Misty Mountain
A shroud of mist
cloaks the summit,
a veil of dreams veils the peaks.
Silent guardians stand watch,
touched by the breath of clouds,
a world untouched, unseen,
yet alive with whispered tales,
where every stone tells a story.

- Violet Ashcroft
